Text:
@brownrl: true, RAR is useful there
On the bittorrent network however it really breaks usability of certain features (selecting only the files you want for download) and corruption checking and fixing is provided by BitTorrent also (in a more efficient way) so that wouldn't be an argument to stick with RAR when seeding it from a RARed source.

The only real (entirely valid) argument for using RARs on bittorrent is plain lazyness to extract it.
